name: Jumping Jacks
description:
This canyon is described in limited detail in Canyons Near Sydney by Rick Jamieson. Help the Australian canyoning community by contributing track notes to ropewiki.com

One of many errors in the Rick Jamieson guidebook - the grid reference is in the wrong creek. That error would've been perpetuated from the Dave Noble sketch map, one of very few errors by Dave. It is presumably an error - all of the tributaries in the area are canyons, but one tributary stands out way more than the others as a quality canyon, so that would've been the one named by Dave as Jumping Jacks canyon. It's quite a strange error given all of the features drawn in the surrounding area - the correct creek (the quality canyon) is obvious, but Dave must've had confusion when transferring his "field notes" on to the sketch map.

Approach

Descent

Exit

Red tape
